# MIGRATIONS & DATA

Source: [`docs/CONSTITUTION.md`](docs/CONSTITUTION.md) III, [`docs/TECHNICAL.md`](docs/TECHNICAL.md) §6. Consult `core.mdc` first.

**Do not load EF or database-performance skills** — schema rules live in Constitution III and Tech §6.

- `postgres-mcp` — read-only MCP queries against running Postgres (procedure only)

**Engine:** PostgreSQL 17 · **Schema:** `app` · **Redis:** session cache only (not migrated via EF)

## EF Core rules

- One migration per logical change; **never edit** a migration already merged — add a new file
- Live under `Solution.Infrastructure/Migrations/`
- Generate:

```bash
dotnet ef migrations add <Name> \
  -p src/Infrastructure/Solution.Infrastructure.csproj \
  -s src/Api/Solution.Api.csproj
```

- **Dev:** apply on service startup (Development)

## Schema essentials

- Tables: `users`, `user_sessions`
- `row_version` on `users`

## Migration checklist (PR)

- [ ] Matches Tech §6 and EF configurations
- [ ] Additive where possible
- [ ] EF model uses `app` schema; concurrency tokens mapped
- [ ] Handler transaction boundaries still valid

## DON'TS

- ❌ No cross-store PG+Redis transactions
- ❌ No hand-editing merged migration snapshots to "fix" history
- ❌ No `Down()` reliance in dev beyond local experiments — prefer roll-forward
